first attempt:

pandoc -V geometry:margin=1.5in chap-definitions.md -o paper.doc --bibliography=../Biblio/cartogis.bib --csl=../Biblio/csl/apa-5th-edition.csl --pdf-engine=xelatex

-- set margins, fonts (Noticia Text 12, Fira sans for diagrams), indentation, paper size? (B4?) -- all should be done via reference doc like this:

pandoc chap-definitions.md -o paper.docx --bibliography=../Biblio/cartogis.bib --csl=../Biblio/csl/apa-5th-edition.csl --pdf-engine=xelatex --reference-doc=reference.docx

combine muliple sources
pandoc -s input1.md input2.md input3.md -o output.html

use extensions, or alternative formats
pandoc -f markdown+extension
-- but some do not output to docx, previous md to md is needed, e.g. for smart, auto_identifiers, etc.
--for inline notes:

pandoc -f markdown+inline_notes chap-definitions.md -o build/paper.docx --bibliography=../Biblio/cartogis.bib --csl=../Biblio/csl/apa-5th-edition.csl --pdf-engine=xelatex --reference-doc=reference.docx

